Description: Three non-joining fragments (734b made up of two joining sherds) of East Greek, perhaps Fikellura, vase of uncertain shape; upper wall offset from bowl; cream slip; interior reserved; exterior:frieze of broad lotuses and buds on bowl; above, on 734a, lower body of feline to right, paw resting on a diagonal, on 734c pendent palmette between buds with uncertain object to left; on 734b, perhaps lowest part of a figure to right, large dot rosette and various very worn remains; graffito at bottom of wall.
Curator's comments: Gardner 1888 has the fragments in the wrong order, lacks one and misses the zeta; the second stroke in his lambda is not clearly intentional. C.A. Hutton, 'Inscriptions on pottery from Naukratis' Classical Review 7 (1893) 83 has the reading ]ιτν[ for the final inscribed fragment.
Bibliographic references: Bernand 1970 / Le Delta égyptien d'après les textes grecs, i: les confins libyques (p. 677, no. 360, pl. 30)
Schlotzhauer 2012 / Untersuchungen zur archaischen griechischen Keramik aus Naukratis (p. 150, NAU 119, pl. 26a-b)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GE.961)
